.TH "TEMPORAL.PLAINDATE.FROM" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.PlainDate.from \- Temporal.PlainDate.from()
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]Temporal.PlainDate.from()\f[B]\f[R] static method creates
a new \f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R] object from another
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R] object, an object with date properties, or
an RFC 9557 string.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
Temporal.PlainDate.from(info)
Temporal.PlainDate.from(info, options)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]info\f[R]
One of the following:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
A \f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R] instance, which creates a copy of the
instance.
.IP \(bu 2
A \f[CR]Temporal.PlainDateTime\f[R] instance, which provides the
calendar date in the same fashion as
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDateTime.prototype.toPlainDate()\f[R].
.IP \(bu 2
A \f[CR]Temporal.ZonedDateTime\f[R] instance, which provides the
calendar date in the same fashion as
\f[CR]Temporal.ZonedDateTime.prototype.toPlainDate()\f[R].
.IP \(bu 2
An RFC 9557 string containing a date and optionally a calendar.
.IP \(bu 2
An object containing the following properties (in the order they are
retrieved and validated):
.RS 2
.TP
\f[B]calendar\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
A string that corresponds to the \f[CR]calendarId\f[R] property.
See \f[CR]Intl.supportedValuesOf()\f[R] for a list of commonly supported
calendar types.
Defaults to \f[CR]\(dqiso8601\(dq\f[R].
All other properties are interpreted in this calendar system (unlike the
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate()\f[R] constructor, which interprets the values
in the ISO calendar system).
.TP
\f[B]day\f[R]
An integer that corresponds to the \f[CR]day\f[R] property.
Must be positive regardless of the \f[CR]overflow\f[R] option.
.TP
\f[B]era\f[R] and \f[B]eraYear\f[R]
A string and an integer that correspond to the \f[CR]era\f[R] and
\f[CR]eraYear\f[R] properties.
Are only used if the calendar system has eras.
\f[CR]era\f[R] and \f[CR]eraYear\f[R] must be provided simultaneously.
At least one of \f[CR]eraYear\f[R] (together with \f[CR]era\f[R]) or
\f[CR]year\f[R] must be provided.
If all of \f[CR]era\f[R], \f[CR]eraYear\f[R], and \f[CR]year\f[R] are
provided, they must be consistent.
.TP
\f[B]month\f[R]
Corresponds to the \f[CR]month\f[R] property.
Must be positive regardless of the \f[CR]overflow\f[R] option.
At least one of \f[CR]month\f[R] or \f[CR]monthCode\f[R] must be
provided.
If both \f[CR]month\f[R] and \f[CR]monthCode\f[R] are provided, they
must be consistent.
.TP
\f[B]monthCode\f[R]
Corresponds to the \f[CR]monthCode\f[R] property.
At least one of \f[CR]month\f[R] or \f[CR]monthCode\f[R] must be
provided.
If both \f[CR]month\f[R] and \f[CR]monthCode\f[R] are provided, they
must be consistent.
.TP
\f[B]year\f[R]
Corresponds to the \f[CR]year\f[R] property.
At least one of \f[CR]eraYear\f[R] (together with \f[CR]era\f[R]) or
\f[CR]year\f[R] must be provided.
If all of \f[CR]era\f[R], \f[CR]eraYear\f[R], and \f[CR]year\f[R] are
provided, they must be consistent.
The info should explicitly specify a year (as \f[CR]year\f[R] or
\f[CR]era\f[R] and \f[CR]eraYear\f[R]), a month (as \f[CR]month\f[R] or
\f[CR]monthCode\f[R]), and a day.
.RE
.RE
.TP
\f[B]options\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
An object containing the following property:
.RS
.TP
\f[B]overflow\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
A string specifying the behavior when a date component is out of range
(when using the object \f[CR]info\f[R]).
Possible values are:
.RS
.TP
\f[B]\(dqconstrain\(dq\f[R] (default)
The date component is clamped to the valid range.
.TP
\f[B]\(dqreject\(dq\f[R]
A \f[CR]RangeError\f[R] is thrown if the date component is out of range.
.RE
.RE
.SS Return value
A new \f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R] object, representing the date
specified by \f[CR]info\f[R] in the specified \f[CR]calendar\f[R].
.SS Exceptions
.TP
\f[B]TypeError\f[R]
Thrown in one of the following cases:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]info\f[R] is not an object or a string.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]options\f[R] is not an object or \f[CR]undefined\f[R].
.IP \(bu 2
The provided properties are insufficient to unambiguously determine a
date.
You usually need to provide a \f[CR]year\f[R] (or \f[CR]era\f[R] and
\f[CR]eraYear\f[R]), a \f[CR]month\f[R] (or \f[CR]monthCode\f[R]), and a
\f[CR]day\f[R].
.RE
.TP
\f[B]RangeError\f[R]
Thrown in one of the following cases:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
The provided properties that specify the same component are
inconsistent.
.IP \(bu 2
The provided non\-numerical properties are not valid; for example, if
\f[CR]monthCode\f[R] is never a valid month code in this calendar.
.IP \(bu 2
The provided numerical properties are out of range, and
\f[CR]options.overflow\f[R] is set to \f[CR]\(dqreject\(dq\f[R].
.IP \(bu 2
The info is not in the representable range, which is ±(10\(ha8 + 1)
days, or about ±273,972.6 years, from the Unix epoch.
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Creating a PlainDate from an object
.IP
.EX
\f[I]// Year, month, and day\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] d1 = Temporal.PlainDate.from({ year: 2021, month: 7, day: 1 });
console.log(d1.toString()); \f[I]// \(dq2021\-07\-01\(dq\f[R]

\f[I]// Year, month code, and day\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] d2 = Temporal.PlainDate.from({ year: 2021, monthCode: \(dqM07\(dq, day: 1 });
console.log(d2.toString()); \f[I]// \(dq2021\-07\-01\(dq\f[R]

\f[I]// Year, month, day in a different calendar\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] d3 = Temporal.PlainDate.from({
  year: 2021,
  month: 7,
  day: 1,
  calendar: \(dqchinese\(dq,
});
\f[I]// Note: when you construct a date with an object, the date components\f[R]
\f[I]// are in *that* calendar, not the ISO calendar. However, toString() always\f[R]
\f[I]// outputs the date in the ISO calendar. For example, the year \(dq2021\(dq in\f[R]
\f[I]// the Chinese calendar is actually 616 BC in the ISO calendar.\f[R]
console.log(d3.toString()); \f[I]// \(dq\-000616\-08\-12[u\-ca=chinese]\(dq\f[R]

\f[I]// Era, eraYear, month, and day\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] d4 = Temporal.PlainDate.from({
  era: \(dqmeiji\(dq,
  eraYear: 4,
  month: 7,
  day: 1,
  calendar: \(dqjapanese\(dq,
});
console.log(d4.toString()); \f[I]// \(dq1871\-07\-01[u\-ca=japanese]\(dq\f[R]
.EE
.SS Controlling overflow behavior
By default, out\-of\-range values are clamped to the valid range:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] d1 = Temporal.PlainDate.from({ year: 2021, month: 13, day: 1 });
console.log(d1.toString()); \f[I]// \(dq2021\-12\-01\(dq\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] d2 = Temporal.PlainDate.from({ year: 2021, month: 2, day: 29 });
console.log(d2.toString()); \f[I]// \(dq2021\-02\-28\(dq\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] d3 = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2021\-02\-29\(dq);
console.log(d3.toString()); \f[I]// \(dq2021\-02\-28\(dq\f[R]
.EE
.PP
You can change this behavior to throw an error instead:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] d3 = Temporal.PlainDate.from(
  { year: 2021, month: 13, day: 1 },
  { overflow: \(dqreject\(dq },
);
\f[I]// RangeError: date value \(dqmonth\(dq not in 1..12: 13\f[R]
.EE
.SS Creating a PlainDate from a string
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] d = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01\(dq);
console.log(d.toLocaleString(\(dqen\-US\(dq, { dateStyle: \(dqfull\(dq }));
\f[I]// Thursday, July 1, 2021\f[R]

\f[I]// Providing a calendar\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] d2 = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01[u\-ca=japanese]\(dq);
console.log(
  d2.toLocaleString(\(dqja\-JP\(dq, { calendar: \(dqjapanese\(dq, dateStyle: \(dqfull\(dq }),
);
\f[I]// 令和3年7月1日木曜日\f[R]

\f[I]// Providing a time and an offset (ignored)\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] d3 = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01T00:00+08:00\(dq);
console.log(d3.toString()); \f[I]// \(dq2021\-07\-01\(dq\f[R]
.EE
.SS Creating a PlainDate from another Temporal instance
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] dt = Temporal.PlainDateTime.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01T12:00\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] d = Temporal.PlainDate.from(dt);
console.log(d.toString()); \f[I]// \(dq2021\-07\-01\(dq\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] zdt = Temporal.ZonedDateTime.from(
  \(dq2021\-07\-01T00:00+08:00[Asia/Shanghai]\(dq,
);
\f[B]const\f[R] d2 = Temporal.PlainDate.from(zdt);
console.log(d2.toString()); \f[I]// \(dq2021\-07\-01\(dq\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] d3 = Temporal.PlainDate.from(d);
console.log(d3.toString()); \f[I]// \(dq2021\-07\-01\(dq\f[R]
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
